Chukrasia velutina

    Authority   Wt. & Arn
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Meliaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4548

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Joshi H 1980a pp 160-164 [TEMP, RAIN, DEP, DRA, TEXT, USE, PH]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial evergreen or deciduous tree, leafless in cold weather. In
   India, the tree flower in April-May, and the capsules ripen from
   December to March.
   COMMON NAMES
   Chickrassy, Chittagong red wood, Boga poma, Chikrassi, Padda, Dalmara,
   Kalgarige, Karadi, Akil, Chuvannagli, Malaveppu, Padda, Lal devadagri,
   Madagirivembum, Agal, Malei-veppu.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: C. tabularis. The tree can reach a height of 15-30
   m. In India adapted to a relative humidity in January from 45-90%, and
   ind July from 70-100%. Chickrassy can be found at elevations from sea
   level to 750 m. It is shade tolerant in the early stages.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
